Kenya Pipeline Company managing director Joe Sang,  has finally bowed to boardroom pressure and will now not seek a second term at the helm of the corporation. Sang has been on the spotlight over the alleged loss over 11 million litters of fuel ,worth Billions of shillings through spillage. The board also invited the Directorate of Criminal Investigation to probe the loss of public funds at the corporation which is also the subject of a probe by  relevant parliamentary committees .   